  <h2>Ad-Hoc Link Tracking</h2> 
  <p>Ad-hoc link tracking allows content authors to configure link tracking for a component. The configuration of the component overrides the <strong>Link Tracking Configuration</strong> of the framework, so on pages that are associated with the framework, <strong>Text</strong> components can be configured for link tracking of URLs.</p> 
  <p>Ad-hoc link tracking enables you to track download links, external links, together with event and variables data. </p> 
  <p>To enable ad-hoc link tracking you need to:<br /> </p> 
  <ul> 
   <li><a href="../../../sites/administering/using/adobeanalytics-connect.md#associatingapagewithaadobeanalyticsframework">Associate the page that contains the <strong>Text</strong> component with the framework</a>.</li> 
   <li><a href="#enablingadhoclinktracking">Configure the Adobe Analytics framework to enable ad-hoc link tracking</a>.</li> 
   <li><a href="#configuringlinktrackingforatextcomponent">Configure Link Tracking for a Text component</a>.<br /> </li> 
  </ul> 
